<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 17 at 9:23PM CDT until April 18 at 12:00AM CDT by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 945 PM CDT
FOR BUTLER AND SOUTHEASTERN WILCOX COUNTIES...
At 922 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles west of
Greenville, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Half dollar size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Greenville, Georgiana and Pine Apple.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.25 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
